    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-01-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-01-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="851"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d851">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-01-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 31, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Leishman reports that a note has just been delivered by the powers in regard
                    to the Macedonian reforms, and that the withdrawal <pb facs="0907" n="819"
                        xml:id="pg_819"/> of the American fleet will be made at an opportune moment
                    and will have a good general effect, but no immediate settlement of the pending
                    questions can be expected, as the above-mentioned note has caused a political
                    crisis and will prevent consideration of other business for the present. The
                    withdrawal of the fleet is accepted by the minister for foreign affairs as a
                    most friendly act on the part of the Government, and he has given assurances
                    that the withdrawal will be greatly appreciated, and that he will use his best
                    endeavors to obtain a settlement of the pending questions at the first opportune
                    moment. Mr. Leishman requests to be informed of the date of departure of the
                    fleet.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
